## Key Takeaways

1. Speed is your entry ticket. AI systems don’t just rank pages; they first have to "fetch" them. If your site takes too long to load, the AI simply cuts the connection and moves on to a faster site. You don’t get a ranking penalty—you get ignored entirely.

2. The "499" error is the red flag. This is the technical code for "the visitor (the AI) left before the page finished loading." If your analytics show high 499 errors, your site is too slow for AI agents.

3. AI is impatient. Unlike human users who might wait a few seconds, AI bots are built to be incredibly fast. They scan many sites at once, and they have no patience for a sluggish server or heavy code.

